prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The John D. Rockefeller papers were given to the Rockefeller Archive Center by the Rockefeller Brothers in 1976.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The John D. Rockefeller papers are open for scholarly research.
Brittle or damaged items, or materials otherwise in need of preservation care, may be closed to researchers at the discretion of RAC.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Subseries FV primarily contains financial vouchers documenting the activities of John D. Rockefeller and John D. Rockefeller Jr. in the late 19th and early 20th century.
